<div class='headline center-block'>
  <img src='/images/logo-big.png' class='img-responsive' alt="Books 4 Equality">
  <p class='lead'>Your Free Textbook Library</p>
</div>

<div class='jumbotron'>
  <p class='lead'>
	Books4Equality aims to provide equal access to textbooks for everyone. For FREE!
  </p>
  <p>We lend you books for the semester at no cost, so you can focus on classes.
  </p>
	<div class='sub-section'>
		<h4>Get Your Books</h4>
		<p>The first week of classes <span class='bold'>(Tuesday the 19th - Friday the 22nd)</span> we'll be givingaway books in the <span class="bold">Davis Center 10:00am-2:00pm</span><p>
		<h5>How do you get them?</h5>
		<ul>
			<li>Make an account on this website to reserve a book. (It's very early days for this feature & it might not be perfect yet). </li>
				<ul>
					<li>You can also just drop by our table with no reservation</li>
				</ul>
			<li>Come by the Davis Center to pick up your books. See schedule below for what subjects are offered on what days</li>
				<ul>
					<li>If you miss the day, send us an email with your request <a href="mailto:books4equality@gmail.com">Books4Equality@gmail.com</a></li>
				</ul>
		</ul>
		<h6>Schedule</h6>
		<p class="italic">(Numbers in parentheses are the Dewey Decimal Numbers)</p>
		<ul>
			<li><span class="bold">Tuesday:</span> History, Literature, Art, Psychology (100, 700, 800, 900)</li>
			<li><span class="bold">Wednesday:</span> Engineering, Human Health and Anatomy, Accounting (600)</li>
			<li><span class="bold">Thursday:</span> Social Sciences: Statistics, Poli Science, Econonomics (300)</li>
			<li><span class="bold">Friday:</span> Science and Math (500)</li>
		</ul>
		<p>If you have books to donate, we would love to take them off your hands</p>
		
	</div>
	
